    faq_a: `Motorized shading with occupancy-aware scheduling is particularly useful in Solana Beach where daytime privacy from close neighbors is an ongoing concern rather than an evening-only one. iL Progetto programs motorized systems to deploy privacy shades during the midday hours when neighboring homes' windows are most active and retract them in the morning and evening when privacy risk is lower. Battery-powered motors on Solana Beach's varied housing stock — from compact beach cottages to Cedros-adjacent design homes — retrofit without electrical work. Voice control and app adjustment also let homeowners override the schedule instantly.`,
