    faq_a: `Blackout curtains with side returns and a ceiling-mount track address both problems simultaneously in Solana Beach bedrooms with close-proximity neighbors. The triple-pass blackout lining blocks all light transmission including early coastal dawn; the ceiling-mount bracket configuration with side returns closes the gap at panel edges that would otherwise create a light blade visible from the neighboring property at night. iL Progetto designs the track and return configuration to your specific window geometry and neighbor proximity angle for maximum effectiveness.`,
