    faq_q: `Can zebra shades work in a Spanish Colonial estate in Rancho Santa Fe without looking out of place?`,
    faq_a: `The key for RSF's Spanish Colonial and Mediterranean homes is fabric tone selection — zebra shades in warm ivory, linen-white, and warm taupe horizontal bands integrate with the arched windows and terracotta surfaces of Covenant architecture far better than the cool grays and bright whites that read as contemporary. iL Progetto selects zebra shade fabrics in the warm neutral colorways that harmonize with RSF's architectural vocabulary and specifies cassette finishes in the bronze and warm-metal tones that the ARB has consistently approved. Estate-scale window heights are accommodated with extended drop fabrication.`,
