    faq_a: `Woven wood shades in bamboo, jute, and rattan constructions have a strong design precedent in hacienda and Spanish Colonial interiors — the organic texture, warm amber tones, and handcrafted quality align naturally with hand-painted tile floors, exposed beam ceilings, and ironwork hardware that define RSF's Covenant architecture. iL Progetto sources woven wood materials in the warm honey and tobacco tones that harmonize with Spanish Colonial palettes and adds privacy lining for bedrooms and guest rooms where the open weave alone is insufficient. For ARB-reviewed applications, the natural material reads as traditionally appropriate.`,
