    faq_a: `The Rancho Santa Fe ARB evaluates exterior sun screens on frame color, mesh color, and cassette finish. iL Progetto selects screen specifications within the warm neutral and earthy tone range that the Covenant ARB has consistently approved — typically dark bronze mesh in anodized aluminum frames — and prepares submittal documentation with color samples and installation elevations. Rancho Santa Fe's inland location means south-facing windows face more intense heat gain than coastal communities, and 3–5% openness screens provide meaningful solar rejection for the large glazed areas common in RSF estate architecture.`,
